{
  "stem": "15962.2",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I would like to go back and fill in a couple of points about the first couple of years of the occupation.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Many Jews tried to leave for other countries, particularly England, the United States, and Palestine.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And some were very fortunate to succeed very early on when there was still a somewhat of a confusion, although borders were closed very quickly.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So it was a question of obtaining valid visas for the country of destination.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Several of my cousins, and even an uncle, happened to be abroad on a business trip.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And they tried to get their families out of the country.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Some succeeded.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Others did not.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "As did others, my mother, who was a more active member of our family and less resigned to fate, went to Prague many times to ob-- to try and obtain visas.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And we actually had a visa for, for [NON-ENGLISH] at the time.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But my father was very reluctant to leave.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And I couldn't tell you now what the real reason is why we didn't leave, whether it was too late or whether we could not get transit visas.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "The history of that period is very sad, because most countries had very restrictive immigration laws and did not want the Jews to come and compete with the depressed labor market or for any other reasons.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "There were only limited privileged people who were granted visas.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And I actually benefited by the unfilled places of immigration after the war when I left for Canada.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "So a great deal of effort and probably money was put into trying to leave the country.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "My uncle, who was on a trip abroad, went to Palestine from England and then got his wife and child out.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "A couple of other cousins didn't succeed.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
